name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Grenze Thin'.

Grenze Thin Italic (Grenze-ThinItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Grenze-ThinItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Grenze Thin Italic (Grenze-ThinItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin Italic' = NID 1 'Grenze Thin' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Grenze ExtraLight Regular (Grenze-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight' = NID 1 'Grenze ExtraLight'.

Pass

Grenze ExtraLight Italic (Grenze-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Grenze-ExtraLightItalic', Everything looks good.

Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Grenze-ExtraLightItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Grenze ExtraLight Italic (Grenze-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight Italic' = NID 1 'Grenze ExtraLight' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Grenze-Light', Everything looks good.

Pass

Grenze Light Regular (Grenze-Light.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light' = NID 1 'Grenze Light'.

Pass

Grenze Light Italic (Grenze-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light Italic' = NID 1 'Grenze Light' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

, most common Monotype license test is:
This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. You can learn more about Monotype by clicking here: www.monotype.com.

Grenze Italic (Grenze-Italic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Grenze-Italic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Grenze Medium Regular (Grenze-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Grenze-Medium', Everything looks good.

Pass

Grenze Medium Regular (Grenze-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Grenze Medium'.

Pass

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.

NID 6 is 'Grenze-MediumItalic', Everything looks good.

Grenze Medium Italic (Grenze-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'Grenze Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Grenze SemiBold Regular (Grenze-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Grenze SemiBold'.

NID 6 is 'Grenze-SemiBoldItalic', Everything looks good.

MS NID 0, Copyright.

It should follow this structure: 'Copyright (c) XXXX - XXXX /entity/. All rights reserved.'

Grenze SemiBold Italic (Grenze-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Grenze-SemiBoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Grenze SemiBold Italic (Grenze-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold Italic' = NID 1 'Grenze SemiBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Mac NID 6

NID 6 is 'Grenze-Bold', Everything looks good.

Grenze Bold Italic (Grenze-BoldItalic.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Grenze-BoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

NID 6 is 'Grenze-BoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Grenze ExtraBold Regular (Grenze-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Grenze-ExtraBold', Everything looks good.

Grenze ExtraBold Regular (Grenze-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Grenze-ExtraBold', Everything looks good.

Pass

Grenze ExtraBold Regular (Grenze-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold' = NID 1 'Grenze ExtraBold'.

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold Italic' = NID 1 'Grenze ExtraBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Mac NID 6

Grenze Black Regular (Grenze-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black' = NID 1 'Grenze Black'.

Pass

Grenze Black Italic (Grenze-BlackItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Grenze-BlackItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Grenze Black Italic (Grenze-BlackItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Grenze' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Black Italic' = NID 1 'Grenze Black' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass
